
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Introduction
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    Locates and provides access to .NET frameworks and tools for executing
    and compiling .NET assemblies.



--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Implementations
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    Supports various implementations of the .NET framework, including
    Microsoft .NET and Mono:

        http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/.NET_Framework

        http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mono_%28software%29



--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Generations
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    Supports multiple generations of .NET corresponding to the .NET framework
    versions shipped by Microsoft:

        http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/.NET_Framework_version_history



--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Frameworks and Tools
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    Globally, the module locates frameworks and tools available on the
    system.  It then provides project variables with options and sensible
    defaults for implementation, generation, and tools.



--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Common .NET Compilation Variables
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    The module provides project variables for common .NET aspects that can
    (but need not) be used by other modules that compile .NET assemblies.
    These include an output directory; required libraries from the GAC and
    from other projects; common compilation options like debug and optimize;
    minimum framework generation; output filenames; and others.



